2280324250059101690.name: Achill Island
2280324250059101690.description: We passed Pine Island in Connemara, one of the most beautiful features in the area. Not coincidentally, it is also one of the few patches of land inaccessible to sheep-grazing.

7717728344473949070.name: London
7717728344473949070.description: One of the stranger residents of london are the pelicans of St. James Park. They were introduced in 1664 by the Russian Ambassador, and since then have surprised tourists by occasionally eating Pigeons

-4055545282759162589.name: Roundstone
-4055545282759162589.description: These photos are from a trip though Connemara to Roundstone. I was using a bridge camera, so the image quality (and corrective editing) is questionable

-1139003324641964013.name: Edinburgh
-1139003324641964013.description: I visited to see the Giant Pandas Yang Guang and Tian Tian before they were recalled to China. Sadly, I was only succesful in seeing them turnt away in a corner sleeping. The red panda was thankfully more photogenic

2286686689568492280.name: London Wetland Centre
2286686689568492280.description: The London Wetland Centre was suitable named; it was pouring when I visited. I managed to see the large lapwing population that visits during winter, and some unexpected eurasian cranes

-4049536796133789550.name: Bray Air Show
-4049536796133789550.description: It is impressive how a stunt pilot can deliberately stall, flat spin, and generally abuse their plane while staying in the air. For a few moments I was genuinely worried they would drop into the Irish Sea.

-4491595777574970180.name: Rutting Season, Killarney
-4491595777574970180.description: Killarney is home to the last native red deer in Ireland. In "rutting season", the stags bellow and battle each other for mates. I risked getting close (at some personal risk) to get better photos, until an extremely irritated park ranger caught up to me. But at that point, I had the photos!

-3003010087158034523.name: Chester Zoo
-3003010087158034523.description: I was lucky enough to see the small-clawed otters at feeding time. They were extremely noisy and pleased by their meals, and I got a few cute videos and pictures

-5315952208455423094.name: Ballyfin Nature Hide
-5315952208455423094.description: Midwinter wildlife photography is challenging in Ireland; there just isn't enough light for much of the day. Lighting aside, I got extremely lucky and managed to get a picture of our elusive (but recovering) pine-marten

-6812976272012837947.name: Lapwings, Emo, Laois
-6812976272012837947.description: Lapwings are Ireland's national bird. Their population has declined due to habitat loss and changes in farming practice (they are ground-nesting like curlews). I was lucky enough to see a few lapwings in a ploughed field near Emo, Co. Laois. They are graceful fliers and have an especially beautiful song

-8066421235976360205.name: Dublin Zoo
-8066421235976360205.description: I visited Dublin Zoo to get a picture of the recently arrived Dhole - a red-brown asian canine. It thankfully posed for me.

7993090020621169568.name: International Crane Foundation, Wisconsin
7993090020621169568.description: After visiting the International Crane Foundation, I have the rare accolade of having seen every extant crane species on the planet

3421749721138658673.name: Wisconsin
3421749721138658673.description: The biodiversity and presence of nature in Wisconsin was surprising. Practically every lamp-post had a percehd red-tailed hawk, vultures were circling over the fields, and there were several osprey over the lakes. The abundance of nature was enviable from an Irish perspective

4604611662163557930.name: Ballyfin Nature Hide
4604611662163557930.description: During this visit to Ballyfin Nature Hide I managed to get some nice photos of our native red squirrel. The invasive grey squirrel population is more common in the east, but fortunately it seems that the slower grey squirrels cannot coexist with pine-martens while our red squirrels can

4410708596887019718.name: Irish Air Corps Centenary Airshow
4410708596887019718.description: I got a free ticket to this airshow; the formations flew by my apartment and I noticed after a few helicopters flew by

7123079405063457843.name: Grand Canal, Dublin
7123079405063457843.description: One of the locals along the Grand Canal feeds herons fish every day, so the buildings are sentied by herons waiting for dinner. I doubt she's popular with her neighbours; herons are colloquially known as 'shitepokes' due to their habit of ... when taking off. The paint-jobs of the expensive cars here are somewhat tarnished

1745882055465401236.name: Lincoln Park Zoo, Chicago
1745882055465401236.description: I saw a large number of wasps in the bushes in Lincoln Park Zoo. I wanted a photo, but as a rule of thumb, large nest-building wasps are fairly aggressive. I quickly searched Wikipedia, and made a plausible guess at the species (Sphex pensylvanicus, the great black wasp). It appeared to be a digger wasp, and by my theory should be fairly friendly. Thankfully, they didn't prove me wrong.

7947351624503440732.name: Skellig Micheal
7947351624503440732.description: Skellig Micheal is rocky crag off the cost of Kerry. It's a UNESCO World Heritage Site with a large (and farely tame) puffin population

6410433821919625210.name: Lough Atalia
6410433821919625210.description: Lough Atalia was the first place I noticed the resurgence of egrets in Ireland. They started nesting in Ireland in 1997, and have become increasingly common since then.

-3510341468605915399.name: Saltee Islands
-3510341468605915399.description: The Saltee islands are a pair of privately-owned islands south of County Wexford. It has recently been granted the Special Protection Area to protect the bird habitat, which from my photos includes puffins, gulls, gormorants, gannets, and razorbills.

4453788876553783742.name: Dalkey Island
4453788876553783742.description: Dalkey Island is home to the red-listed roseate tern, and a herd of feral goats that I was informed have become more friendly since people started feeding them regularly

images.description: This tram is in regular service. I'm really glad to have went on it, but it's not the most comfortable way to travel

5899238330198681938.name: Swifts & Martins
5899238330198681938.description: I spotted these birds getting a taxi from South Dublin to the centre. The next day, I spent the afternoon squinting at the sun and spinning in circles trying to get the birds in focus.

1888329774390600928.name: Burr Point
1888329774390600928.description: Burr Point is the easternmost point of mainland Ireland.
